Harlequin wrote:

>>Amend Rule 1579 ("Mintors") by adding the text:

      All Players have Mint Authority.<<

I am sceptical about a simple reintroduction of this mint
authority. All of Morendil's Mint Manipulation is based not on a
loophole in the PC rules, but on a hole that resides at least partly
in the minting rules: That a player can create nomic entities with any
names e wants, and that via a suitable naming conflict this can mess
up the results of proposals which are just being voted on. Such
attacks are possible against all proposals that introduce new nomic
entities, and they remain so now (wonder what Morendil will mint next
... :)

Of course, refusing players mint authority is useless to prevent
further scams like the MMM, as long as groups' executors still have
that power. 

But as a response to the MMM something somewhere has to be changed. I
would prefer this change to happen in the naming and/or definition of
nomic entities, but still I feel we should solve this first before we
restore minting rights. So I would suggest the opposite regulation for
a first cleanup: deny minting rights to groups as well as players. 

