>because the former is a physical manipulation to which the Monopoly tokens
are
>entirely impervious; just standing around shouting silly things is not going
>to move no poker chips around. Whereas _all_ manipulations of physical
>entities that are relevant to our playing Agora consist of sending
messages of
>one sort or another, and it is a very difficult matter to tell which of
these 
>manipulations are legal and which are not.

I don't see the difference. The only reason it is more difficult to
determine the legality of such posts in Agora is because the Rules
regarding money in Agora are far more complex. Should you successfully
convince the Recordkeepor that you should actually receive that 1 VT, even
if the Rules don't say so, you *will.* In Monopoly, if you convince the
other players that the rules would have given you that $100, even if in
reality they don't, you still would get the $100. 


