Actually that's not quite right - the Implicit TO Rules in fact dictate that
such a message should be considered to be a request of the Assessor to record
a delayed transfer of one VT from the Player casting a Vote to the Bank (and,
in fact, additionally the submission of a request that any previous such TOs
should be vacated). The voting message itself doesn't _cause_ a transfer, it is
deemed to be equivalent to _requiring_ one, a subtle distinction. 

