But transfers in Monopoly are easily trackable. On your turn, you ask a few
questions. Did you land on someone else's property? Did you land on Chance
or Community Chest? Did you land on Free Parking? Did you pass Go? Did you
mortgage any Property? They're all directly related to the game actions you
have performed on your turn. In Agora, transfers and requirements to make
transfers occur at any time, and because of the semi-automated nature of
the game, are much more difficult to track and record. 

